seriously, when a driver who led San Diego police on a 15-minute chase crashed 
into a car at 8th Street and Euclid Avenue in National City, setting off a 
chain collision involving six cars. Fausto Medina, 20, was arrested on 
suspicion of felony auto theft and felony hit-and-run driving. Police said the 
suspect lost a tire and was driving only on a rim toward the end of the chase. 
ROBERT FAABORG 
