VALLEY ROUNDUP: SUPERIOR INDUSTRIES WINS $3-MILLION MAZDA CONTRACT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Superior Industries has received a contract that it estimated to be worth $3 
million annually to produce aluminum wheels for Mazda Motor Corp. Superior, 
based in Van Nuys, said it began shipping the wheels in July for use in Mazda's 
B2000 model mini-pickup. 
