<P>
VALLEY ROUNDUP: INVESTMENT BANK OFFERS $77 MILLION TO BUY SYNCOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Lisle, Ill., investment bank Friday submitted an offer worth about $77 
million to buy Syncor International Corp., the Chatsworth distributor of 
radiopharmaceuticals. 
</P>
<P>
Van Kampen Merritt, the investment bank, said it was making the $7.57-per-share 
bid on behalf of an unnamed client. 
</P>
<P>
Dee Carrington, vice president for home care at Syncor, said the company's 
board would evaluate the offer. 
</P>
<P>
The offer expires Thursday. 
</P>
