VALLEY PEOPLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Delphi Information Systems named Donald L. Lucas as chairman of the Westlake 
Village computer concern, replacing Walter F. Bauer, who retired but remains a 
Delphi director. 
</P>
<P>
Bauer stepped down because he turned 65 and was at the end of a three-year 
contract with Delphi, said Delphi President Richard R. Janssen. Bauer's 
departure was not related to Delphi's recent poor performance, Janssen said. 
</P>
<P>
Delphi, which sells computer systems to property-casualty insurance brokers, 
lost $710,000 on revenue of $20.5 million in its fiscal year that ended March 
31. 
</P>
<P>
Lucas, a venture capitalist and a Delphi director since 1983, also is chairman 
of two computer software companies, Oracle Systems and Cadence Design Systems. 
</P>
