<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: KUDOS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALEENE MacMINN, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Actress Pauline Collins, the star of Paramount's "Shirley Valentine," has 
received a Discovery Award from the Los Angeles Film Teachers Assn. The award 
salutes Collins "for her tour-de-force performance in 'Shirley Valentine,' the 
movie that reminds us how important it is not to lose touch with our dreams," 
said Alice La Deane, LAFTA president. ALEENE MacMINN 
</P>
