<P>
JUDGES SELECTED FOR SANDCASTLE CONTEST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The county chapter of the American Institute of Architects has selected a panel 
of judges for its Oct. 1 sandcastle competition that will include Supervisor 
Thomas F. Riley, Newport Harbor Art Museum director Kevin Consey and Los 
Angeles Times architecture critic Sam Hall Kaplan. 
</P>
<P>
OCCAIA officials said the public event is intended to raise money for the 
organization and "the level of architectural awareness in Orange County." It is 
scheduled to be held from 10 a.m. to 3 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
The other judges selected for the event include architects Ron Yeo, Herb 
Brownell and David Klages; Josie DeFalla, associate director of the Bowers 
Museum; Gifford Myers, professor of art at UC Irvine, and artist Eileen Cowin. 
</P>
<P>
John McMurray, president of OCCAIA, said: "Because of the many professional 
sculptors entered in the competition, the (judges) will have a tough time 
selecting just one first-place winner." 
</P>
<P>
For information on the Invitational Sandcastle Competition, contact Jeff Smith 
at Richard Lewis Architects at (714) 549-2800 or the AIA chapter office at 
(714) 557-7796. 
