<P>
P.M. BRIEFING; 
</P>
<P>
BREWER TO FUND ALCOHOL AWARENESS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
DALLAS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Stung by allegations that concerts sponsored by beer companies encourage minors 
to drink, the nation's biggest brewer said it will donate $250,000 to Students 
Against Driving Drunk in Texas. 
</P>
<P>
The money will help provide SADD chapter start-up kits to all Texas junior and 
senior high schools, Stephen J. Burrows, Anheuser-Busch vice president for 
consumer awareness and education, said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
Anheuser-Busch and Miller Brewing Co. were criticized for sponsoring large 
outdoor music festivals in seven Texas cities over the Labor Day weekend. Both 
brewers took precautions to prevent underage drinking and the events, which 
drew 500,000 people, were without major problems, police said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Brief; Wire 
