<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
BJORN BORG, SINGER EXCHANGE VOWS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MILAN, Italy 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Former Swedish tennis star Bjorn Borg and Italian pop singer Loredana Berte 
exchanged vows in a Protestant church ceremony today, 24 hours after their 
civil wedding at city hall. 
</P>
<P>
A pastor from Berne, Switzerland, celebrated the private Lutheran ceremony in a 
tiny downtown church. Church officials, who spoke under condition of anonymity, 
said about 20 guests attended. They included Borg's parents, his son Robin and 
Adriano Panatta, a former player who captains the Italian Davis Cup team. 
</P>
<P>
As they had been Monday, reporters and photographers were barred from the 
ceremony. An Italian weekly magazine, which had been given exclusive rights to 
the story, employed bodyguards to keep onlookers and reporters outside the iron 
fences of the church. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Loredana Berte 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
